# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Shadow Signals Next.js client application.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version ^2.0.0 using npm
- Added as a dependency in `package.json`
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the new package and its 64 dependencies

### 2. Component Integration
- Modified `app/layout.tsx` to import and integrate the SpeedInsights component
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next';`
- Placed `<SpeedInsights />` component in the root layout's body, following Next.js App Router best practices

### 3. Framework-Specific Configuration
- Used the Next.js-specific import path (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`) as recommended in official documentation
- Integrated at the root layout level to ensure Speed Insights tracks all pages in the application
- Component placement ensures it loads on every page without requiring individual page modifications

